Readme :

On Mac / Linux
-------

1) The automated logger helps you add the current date and time automatically to a text file that you usually open to log some events.

2) All you need to do is : 
	a) make sure you extract all the files on Desktop 
	b) Open the terminal , give permissions to the "log.command" file by using following commands on the terminal
		cd Desktop
		chmod 777 log.command

	c) double click on the log.command file
	d) It will show the date and time at the end of LogFile.txt


On Windows
-----------

1) double click log.bat